You can move all of these method definitions up into the class declaration. It will be much less verbose, since you won't have to keep repeating method signatures and `template<class T>`.

~~~
    template<class T> 
    class SlidingWindow {
      public:
        SlidingWindow(UInt maxCapacity)
        : maxCapacity(maxCapacity)
        {
          NTA_CHECK(maxCapacity > 0);
          // and so on
        }

       // and so on
     }
~~~

```python
def deposition_type_from_request():
    """Return deposition from parsed view arguments."""
    return request.view_args.get(
        'deposition_type', None
    ) or (
        Deposition.get_type(request.view_args.get('uuid')) 
        if request.view_args.get('uuid', None) else None
    )
```

